                                          <Label fx:id="explanationLabel" maxHeight="1.7976931348623157E308" maxWidth="1.7976931348623157E308" styleClass="explanation-text" text="Here is the realistic dummy text for your math problem and the clean CSS.1. The Dummy Text ExplanationPaste this into your &quot;Text Explanation&quot; Label (make sure Wrap Text is checked):Let $B$ be the population of Berryville. Then the population of Appleton is $B + 400$.We are told that if Berryville's population were reduced by 900, Appleton's population would be 3 times as large.We can write this as an equation:$B + 400 = 3 * (B - 900)$$B + 400 = 3B - 2700$$3100 = 2B$$B = 1550$Therefore, the current population of Berryville is 1,550." wrapText="true" />
                                       </children>
                                    </VBox>
